## Notification pattern

The agent does not invoke this tool itself. Instead, the agent:

1. Detects the trigger condition
2. Emits a Telegram notification: "Manual step required: {{tool_name}}.
   Runbook: see `manual/{{tool_id}}.md`. Reply `/done <correlation-id>`
   when finished."
3. Sets `last-run.json status: awaiting-manual` (or runtime-equivalent)
4. Subsequent wakes short-circuit until `/done` lands

This pattern keeps the agent loop intact while gracefully handling
the human-in-the-loop.

